          <p class="ba-sub">For content teams that want to go from research to first draft in 5 minutes — but are willing to edit before publishing.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Scalenut's Cruise Mode takes a keyword and produces a 1,500+ word article in roughly 5 minutes, covering NLP topic research, outline generation, and draft writing. It's fast. It's not autopilot — articles need 20–60% editing before publishing. The $39/month entry price is attractive. Keyword stuffing and robotic tone are consistent complaints.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Research-to-draft in 5 minutes</h4><p>NLP topic research, keyword clustering, and content scoring built in.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>$39/month entry point with 7-day free trial</h4><p>Lowest cost among NLP-optimized content tools.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: requires 20–60% editing before publishing</h4><p>Not autopilot. Robotic tone and keyword stuffing are recurring issues. Platform performance is slow.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

